name: Sudut Kopi
address: Jl. Raya Belega, Belega, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: Sudut Kopi is a great place to relax and enjoy a cup of coffee. The AC space is comfortable and the terrace is perfect for people-watching. The parking in the front of the place. The wifi is fast and reliable, making it a great place to work or study. Most importantly, the coffee is delicious! They use high-quality beans and roast them to perfection. I highly recommend Sudut Kopi Bali to anyone looking for a great place to enjoy a cup of coffee.
review 2: The menu quite diverse, about the taste, the drinks are delicious, especially the Honeydew fresh milk. The foods are good, but need more additional like Cake or maybe Croissant. And the price is super reasonable.
review 3: i tried the moccacino it was good. The place was a bit warm since the direct sunlight makes the place hot during the day. The service was OK. Will come here again just for the drinks. And yes the position of this cafe is really "sudut".
review 4: The food was good, i also order e starberry milk. The place is so good and aesthetic. Best place for hangaout, small parking area but that's fine. Good sercive as well.
review 5: Kind staff, great coffee, indoor(AC)/outdoor(smooking), reasonably cheap price, lots of food option and table games. Definitely one of my go to spot in Gianyar city

name: Warung lawar Sapi Blahbatuh
address: Jl. Bisma, Blahbatuh, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: This is the best (and very rare to find)  Nasi Sapi (Rice and beef meal combo) that we have had  while travelling through Bali. The beef soup is unique and delicious along with the Beef Satay, the unique mince beef lawar and Rice. The place is very clean and the menu is simple so they have perfected this meal combo. It is very popular among the locals. The owners are so nice and kind. The food is also very reasonably priced and super value for money.  We highly recommend it as it certainly worth stopping by to try.
review 2: Great food, friendly owner that speaks English. Beef, satay and soup. Love it! Will be back again.
review 3: This place is so delicious and friendly. Highly recommended!
